---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import PageHero from "../../components/PageHero.astro";
---
<Base
  title="Join the chat"
  description="You're on PalmasMesh — now here's how to talk to your neighbors. How the community channel works, what to say, and the simple courtesies that keep it useful for everyone."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Getting started · Step 3"
    title="You're in. Here's how to talk to your neighbors."
    lede="Your radio's set up and paired. The fun part starts now — actually using PalmasMesh to stay in touch with the people around you."
  />

  <!-- The community channel -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap-narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">The main channel</p>
      <h2>One shared conversation for all of Palmas</h2>
      <p>
        PalmasMesh has a main channel that everyone shares — it's the town
        square. When you send a message there, every neighbor on the network
        sees it, and you see theirs. It works exactly like a group chat you've
        used before, just carried over the radios instead of the Internet.
      </p>
      <p>
        You'll also be able to send a message to one specific neighbor when you
        want a private word, the same way you'd start a one-on-one chat. Both
        kinds of messages are scrambled so only the people they're meant for can
        read them.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How to join the chat (the link) -->
  <section class="section section-dark">
    <div class="wrap-narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">Getting the invite</p>
      <h2>How you actually get added</h2>
      <p class="lede">
        Joining the PalmasMesh channel is a single tap — but you need the invite
        link or QR code from us first. We don't post it publicly, so that the
        network stays a Palmas community rather than the whole Internet.
      </p>
      <div class="join-card">
        <h4>To get the invite:</h4>
        <ol>
          <li>Find us in the <strong>"Meshtastic Puerto Rico"</strong> group on Facebook, or ask a neighbor who's already on the mesh.</li>
          <li>Let us know you're in Palmas del Mar and ready to join.</li>
          <li>We'll send you the PalmasMesh link or QR code. Tap it with your phone, confirm, and you're on the channel.</li>
        </ol>
        <p class="join-note">That link is the same one mentioned in Step 4 of the setup guide — if you've already used it, you're already here.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What to say -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">Once you're in</p>
      <h2>What people actually talk about</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-3 uses">
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Checking in</h4>
          <p>"Everyone okay over by the marina?" A quick all-clear after a storm, or a heads-up when something's going on.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Everyday neighbor stuff</h4>
          <p>Borrowing a ladder, asking which gate's open, a lost dog, a heads-up about the delivery truck at the entrance.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Helping each other on</h4>
          <p>New folks asking setup questions, neighbors sharing where they bought their radio, range tests around the community.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Courtesies -->
  <section class="section" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="wrap-narrow">
      <div class="card courtesy">
        <h3>A few simple courtesies</h3>
        <p>The network is small and shared, so a little consideration keeps it pleasant and quick for everyone.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Keep it short.</strong> Messages travel best when they're brief — a sentence or two beats a paragraph.</li>
          <li><strong>Be a good neighbor.</strong> The same manners you'd want in any group chat. Real names, real kindness.</li>
          <li><strong>Don't flood it.</strong> Avoid sending lots of messages back-to-back; give others room and let the network breathe.</li>
          <li><strong>Save urgent for urgent.</strong> In an emergency the channel is for coordinating and checking in — it doesn't replace 9-1-1 when you can reach it.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Daily use hint -->
  <section class="section section-dark">
    <div class="wrap-narrow center">
      <span class="pill">⬤ Coming soon</span>
      <h2>Reasons to check in every day</h2>
      <p class="lede" style="margin-inline:auto;max-width:46ch;">
        We're putting together community games and regular activities that run
        right on the mesh — small, fun reasons to open the app and say hi. A
        network everyone already uses is a network that's ready when a storm
        hits. Keep an eye on the channel.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .join-card {
      background: var(--tide);
      border: 1px solid var(--line-dk);
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      padding: 1.6rem;
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
    }
    .join-card h4 { color: var(--signal); margin-bottom: 0.8rem; }
    .join-card ol { margin: 0 0 1rem; padding-left: 1.3rem; }
    .join-card li { margin-bottom: 0.6rem; color: var(--mist); }
    .join-card li strong { color: var(--foam); }
    .join-note { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--mist); margin: 0; font-style: italic; }

    .uses { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
    .uses h4 { color: var(--signal); margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }
    .uses p { margin: 0; font-size: 0.96rem; }

    .courtesy ul { margin: 1rem 0 0; padding-left: 1.2rem; }
    .courtesy li { margin-bottom: 0.6rem; }

    .center { text-align: center; }
    .center .pill { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  </style>
</Base>
